ker.Stop(); //task.join(); return 0; }给这些代码加上注释","output":"/* * RollPollingWorker：滚动轮询工作类，用于读取输入文件中的音视频数据，编码后写入输出文件 */ int RollPollingWorker::EncodeFrame(AVFrame* frame) { // 发送AVFrame给编码器进行编码 if (avcodec_send_frame(ocodec_ctx_, frame) < 0) return -1; // 分配一个AVPacket，用于存储编码后的数据 AVPacket* enc_pkt = av_packet_alloc(); int ret = 0; while (ret >= 0) { // 从编码器中读取编码后的数据 ret = avcodec_receive_packet(ocodec_ctx_, enc_pkt); if (ret < 0) { // 暂无数据可读或者数据读完，继续读取 if (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN) || ret == AVERROR_EOF) ret = 0; break; } // 设置AVPacket的一些属性 enc_pkt->stream_index = 0; enc_pkt->pts = enc_pkt->dts = (frame_cnt_++) * 40; enc_pkt->duration = 0; enc_pkt->pos = -1; // 将AVPacket写入输出文件 ret = av_interleaved_write_frame(ofmt_ctx_, enc_pkt); av_packet_unref(enc_pkt); if (ret < 0) { // 写入AVPacket失败 ErrorL << Prefix() << \\" write packet to output file failed n\\"; break; } } av_packet_free(&enc_pkt); return ret; } /* * RollPollingWorkerPool：滚动轮询工作池，用于启动和停止滚动轮询工作 */ int RollPollingWorkerPool::StartWorker(const std::string input, const std::string output) { // 创建RollPollingWorker，启动滚动轮询工作 std::shared_ptr<RollPollingWorker> worker = std::make_shared<RollPollingWorker>(); if (!worker->Start(input, output)) { return -1; } // 将RollPollingWorker加入worker_list_池中 std::weak_ptr<RollPollingWorker> weak_worker = worker; auto task = [weak_worker](int64_t unused){ auto worker = weak_worker.lock(); if (worker) worker->Runnable(); }; std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(mutex_); worker_list_[output] = worker; return 0; } int RollPollingWorkerPool::StopWorker(const std::string url) { // 停止指定输出url的RollPollingWorker std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(mutex_); auto it = worker_list_.find(url); return it != worker_list_.end() ? it->second->Stop() : -1; } int RollPollingWorkerPool::PollingStart(const std::vector<std::string> inputsurl, const std::string outputurl) { std::vector<std::string> inputs = inputsurl ; std::string output = outputurl; mediakit::RollPollingWorker worker; if (worker.Start(inputs[0], output) < 0) return -1; // 启动轮询线程 auto f = [&](){ worker.Runnable(); }; std::thread task(f); task.detach(); size_t idx = 1; while (worker.IsRunning()) { std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(10000)); if (idx >= 4) break; // 轮询切换输入文件 if (inputs.size() > 1) { std::string tmp = inputs[idx % inputs.size()]; std::cerr << \\"change input file to [\\" << tmp << \\"n\\"; worker.UpdateInput(tmp); idx++; } } // 停止RollPollingWorker，并等待轮询线程结束 worker.Stop(); return 0; }"},{"instruction":"test","output":"This is a test response from the OpenAI GPT-3 language model. Is there anything else I can assist you with?"},{"instruction":"Unreal Engine change model scale, how rigid body change","output":"To change the scale of a model in Unreal Engine 4, you can select the actor containing the model and adjust its scale in the Details panel. However, changing the scale of a rigid body in Unreal Engine 4 is a bit different. You can set up the scaling factor using the Physics Asset Editor, which allows you to create and edit physics assets for skeletal meshes. Here\'s how you can scale a rigid body: 1. Open the Physics Asset Editor by double-clicking the skeletal mesh asset in the Content Browser. 2. In the tree view, find the Physics Asset you want to edit and select it. 3. In the details panel, locate and click the Rigid Body node you want to scale. 4. Change the Scale X, Scale Y, or Scale Z values to adjust the rigid body\'s size. 5. Click the Compile button to save your changes. Note that scaling a rigid body will also affect its center of mass, and you may need to adjust it to get the desired physics behavior. You can do this by selecting the Rigid Body node and using the Center of Mass Override options in the Details panel."},{"instruction":"UE 模型非等比缩放，刚体如何变化","output":"要在Unreal Engine 4中对模型进行非等比缩放，您可以选择包含模型的Actor，并在详细信息面板中调整其比例。然而，要改变Unreal Engine 4中刚体的比例则有些不同。 您可以使用物理资产编辑器来设置比例因子，该编辑器允许您为骨骼网格创建和编辑物理资产。以下是如何缩放刚体的方法： 1.通过双击资源浏览器中的骨骼网格资源来打开物理资产编辑器。 2.在树形视图中，找到要编辑的物理资产并选择它。 3.在详细信息面板中，找到并单击要缩放的刚体节点。 4.更改比例值来调整刚体的大小。 5.单击编译按钮以保存更改。 需要注意的是，缩放刚体还会影响其质心，您可能需要调整它以获得所需的物理行为。您可以通过选择刚体节点并在详细信息面板中使用“质心覆盖”选项来完成此操作。"},{"instruction":"blender 刚体的碰撞形状选为网格","output":"在Blender中，将刚体的碰撞形状设置为网格是一种常用的方法。以下是如何将刚体的碰撞形状设置为网格的步骤： 1. 选择您要设置碰撞形状的网格，并单击物体数据属性面板中的“物理”选项卡。 2. 在“物理”选项卡中，展开“碰撞”部分。 3. 在“碰撞”部分中，选择“网格”作为“形状”选项。 4. 如果您的刚体包含多个网格，则可以使用“网格委托”选项来指定哪个网格用作碰撞形状。 5. 调整其他碰撞形状选项，如“网格装甲”和“碰撞边缘”，以匹配您的需求。 完成这些步骤后，您的模型将以其网格形状为基础进行碰撞检测。请注意，使用网格形状作为刚体的碰撞形状可能会影响计算性能，因此在处理大型物体时请务必注意性能问题。"},{"instruction":"blender 刚体的碰撞形状选为网格，为啥场景中看不到刚体","output":"如果您将Blender中的刚体碰撞形状选为网格，并且在场景中看不到刚体，则可能是因为未正确地设置渲染和展示选项。 请按照以下步骤检查： 1. 确认在“物理”选项卡中，您已将网格选为碰撞形状，您也可以展开“呈现”部分，确保“可见性”复选框被选中。 2. 如果刚体的网格导入到了场景中，但是看不到刚体，可以检查刚体是否已经被隐藏或被禁用显示。您可以在3D视图中按“H”来隐藏选定物体，或者您可以检查“可见性”选项在场景中的设置。 3. 您需要确保使用的光源能够照亮刚体。如果刚体所在的区域太暗，可能无法看到它。您可以添加新的光源或更改现有光源的属性来调整照明。 4. 如果仍然无法看到刚体，可能需要检查材质和纹理设置是否正确。请确保刚体使用了正确的材质和纹理，并且存在于需要渲染的图层中。 如果您仍然遇到问题，可以提供更多细节，以便我们更好地帮助您解决问题。"},{"instruction":"呈现部分是是呢嘛","output":"在Blender中，“呈现”部分是指物体的呈现和展示选项。您可以在呈现部分设置物体的可见性、阴影、透明度、颜色等属性。 以下是呈现部分的各个选项的简要说明： 1. 可见性：启用此选项后，物体将可见，并可以在场景中看到。 2. 阴影：启用此选项后，物体将投射阴影。 3. 透明度：此选项允许您设置物体的透明度。您可以使用它来创建透明材质，例如玻璃或水。 4. 颜色：此选项允许您设置物体的颜色。您可以使用它来表示不同的材质或纹理属性。 在物理属性面板中设置物体的碰撞形状为网格之后，您需要在呈现选项中启用“可见性”来显示物体。如果已经启用了“可见性”，则可能需要更改其他呈现选项，如阴影、透明度或颜色，以使物体正确显示在场景中。"},{"instruction":"呈现部分在哪","output":"在Blender中，物体的呈现和展示选项在物体的“属性”编辑器的“对象”选项卡中。要访问呈现部分，请遵循以下步骤： 1. 确保已选定要编辑的物体。 2. 打开属性编辑器。默认情况下，它位于Blender的右侧面板。 3. 在编辑器中，选择“对象”选项卡。 4. 在“对象”选项卡中，您将看到呈现部分，它包括可见性、阴影、透明度、颜色等选项。 在呈现部分，您可以启用或禁用物体的可见性，设置物体是否投射阴影，更改物体的颜色以及调整物体的透明度等视觉选项。 请注意，在“呈现”部分中更改视觉选项仅影响物体在场景中的呈现方式，并不影响物体的物理行为。要更改物体的物理行为，您需要前往Blender中的“物理”选项卡并调整相应的物理属性。"},{"instruction":"i want to create a cmake system","output":"As an AI language model, I can provide some broad steps that you can follow to create a CMake system. Here are the steps: 1. Create a `CMakeLists.txt` file: Create a CMake project by creating a CMakeLists.txt file in the root directory of your project. This file will contain instructions for building your project. 2. Define the project: Use the `project()` command to define your project. This command should go at the top of your CMakeLists.txt file, and it takes a few arguments, such as the name of your project, version of your project, and the programming language you are using. 3. Include additional files: If you need to include additional files or directories in your project, you can use the `include_directories()` or `add_subdirectory()` commands. 4. Define source files: Use the `set()` command to define the source files for your project. You can place the source files in a variable and then reference the variable in other commands. 5. Create targets: Create a target for your project using the `add_executable()` command if your project is an executable or using the `add_library()` command if your project is a library. The command should be followed by the name of the target and the source files. 6. Link libraries: Use the `target_link_libraries()` command to link libraries to your project. You can specify the library’s name and the target that you want to link. 7. Build the project: Run the `cmake` command to generate the build system, and then run the `make` command to build your project. The `cmake --build` command can be used to build your project as well. These are the basic steps to creating a CMake system. However, the actual steps may differ depending on the specific features and requirements of your project."},{"instruction":"I am trying to develop a plugin system for my project, the plugin may depend on some modules inside my project, i provide the static library to plugin developers, the expected result is that plugin developer can use these static libraries provied by my project to create a plugin dll. can you show me the cmakelist.txt","output":"Sure, here is an example of a CMakeLists.txt file for a plugin system that depends on some modules inside your project: ``` cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.6) project(PluginSystem) set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 11) # Set the output directory for the plugin dll set(CMAKE_LIBRARY_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY {CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/bin) # Add the source files for the plugin system set(SOURCES src/plugin.cpp) # Create the plugin dll from the source files add_library(plugin SHARED {SOURCES}) # Link the plugin with the static libraries provided by your project. target_link_libraries(plugin {CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/../lib/module1.lib {CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/../lib/module2.lib ) # Set the include directories for the plugin system include_directories( {CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/include {CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/../include ) ``` In this example, we first set the minimum required version of CMake and the C++ standard to be used. We then set the output directory for the plugin dll to `bin` folder in the source directory. Next, we add the source files for the plugin system in the `src` folder to the `SOURCES` variable. We then use the `add_library()` command to create the plugin dll from the source files. After that, we use the `target_link_libraries()` command to link the plugin with the static libraries provided by your project. In this example, we assume that the static libraries for `module1` and `module2` are available in the `lib` folder relative to the source directory. Finally, we set the include directories for the plugin system using the `include_directories()` command. Here, we assume that the include files for the plugin system and the modules in your project are available in the `include` folder relative to the source directory. Note that this is just an example, and you may need to modify it based on the specific dependencies and requirements of your plugin system."},{"instruction":"there are some display error in your answer, it seems that you can\'t display {} text properly, can you fix it.","output":"I apologize for the formatting issue. Here is the modified version of the CMakeLists.txt file with corrected display: ``` cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.6) project(PluginSystem) s